& [ScaleTiedZeroHeightPolicy] is a project-local finite diagnostic contract
  + [source_snapshot_uuid] is f7dbb7da-49f1-442d-b099-96b2dbef4b15
  + [canonical_specification_uuid] is 9e77d85b-e73a-4cc3-8bb2-c6d834614394
  + [protocol_uuid] is a4ab4ba3-3b1e-45bf-aef6-7df76cf7cd5a
  + [project_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis
  + [active_authority_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop
  + [purpose] is test whether an x-dependent zero-height law such as T = c*log(x) improves explicit-formula residual coordinate behavior compared with fixed T
  + [not_purpose] is proof, disproof, RH evidence, independent zero certification, critical-line authority, universal cutoff-law ranking, or explicit/Euler bridge identity

  = must: use exact finite psi(x), theta(x), and pi(x) rows for sampled x
  = must: compute T from a declared law and expose the law name, multiplier c, and resulting T for each x
  = must: use T = c*log(x) as the first scale-tied law
  = must: include all positive zeta-zero pairs with ordinate gamma <= T for each computed cutoff
  = must: expose the zero_pair_count implied by each computed T
  = must: compare sharp, Fejer, Lanczos, and Hann policies as height-weighted windows of gamma/T
  = must: report best window by x and c, window win counts, sample-level switch counts, and multiplier-transition behavior
  = must: mark output proof_status as finite_scale_tied_zero_height_atlas_not_zero_certification
  = must: treat mpmath zetazero as numerical library lookup, not proof authority
  - never: infer RH proof, disproof, zero certification, or critical-line truth from finite scale-tied residual stability
  - never: collapse local minima into identity
  - never: treat one multiplier or law as universal without a later source-defined broader comparison
  - never: fuse explicit-formula residual rails with Euler-product/log-derivative rails without a later source-defined shared comparison unit

& [ScaleTiedHeightWindowDefinitions] is inherited from T cutoff
  + [sharp] is weight(gamma, T) = 1
  + [fejer] is weight(gamma, T) = 1 - gamma/T
  + [lanczos] is weight(gamma, T) = sin(pi*gamma/T)/(pi*gamma/T)
  + [hann] is weight(gamma, T) = 0.5*(1 + cos(pi*gamma/T))
  + [domain] is 0 < gamma <= T(x)

& [ScaleTiedZeroHeightPolicyTooling] is the implementation scope
